main event: Multiple sightings of UFOs in Houston, Texas on June 19, 1957, including one round object and three objects resembling stars with blue-green light.
interesting points: The UFO varied in color, from light green to red brilliant, and was seen visually for one minute.
Another sighting described three objects resembling stars in a row with blue-green light, with one of the objects seemingly falling apart as if it exploded.
The report indicates that the flight was probably caused by an aircraft, but no further explanation or conclusive evidence was provided.
The sightings were also captured on ground radar, adding credibility to the observations.
The report was addressed to various military and intelligence officials, indicating the significance of the sightings.
sighted object: round object and three star-like objects with blue-green light
witnesses: CAAt Witness, LT Edward P. McCabe, 1/LT Harvey D. Blanton
